The IR JSON Schema, Runtime Implementer's Guide, .termin.pkg package
format specification, and conformance test suite contained in this
repository together define the contract every conforming Termin
runtime must satisfy. The reference implementation lives in the
separate termin-compiler repository
(github.com/jamieleigh3d/termin-compiler) and passes this suite.

This product depends on third-party software, each distributed under
its own open-source license. A non-exhaustive list of test-time
dependencies and their licenses:

  - pytest (MIT)
  - requests (Apache-2.0)
  - jsonschema (MIT)

Optional dependencies for browser-based conformance tests:

  - playwright (Apache-2.0)

The test fixtures under fixtures/ are .termin.pkg archives generated
by the termin-compiler reference implementation. The example source
files from which they were compiled are distributed with termin-compiler
and are themselves Apache-2.0 licensed.

See each dependency's distribution for the full text of its license.
